div.p:
Quantum ad Problema Tuum Ingeniosissimum de transformatione Curvarum Algebraicarum in
          alias propositis longitudine aequales, dixi in ultimis meis, me solutionem in 
 omnibus Parabolis reperisse. En Tibi eam! sint
            x et y coordinatae et a
          Parameter Parabolae Apollonianae, t et u Coordinatae
          Curvae transformatae, erit salvo Calculo, posito
            \sqrt{a^{2m}-y^{2m}}=z^{m};t=\frac{y^{1+m}}{\overline{1+m}a^{m}}-\frac{a^{1-3m}z^{3m}}{\frac{3}{2}m}+\frac{\frac{1}{m}-1,a^{1-5m}z^{5m}}{\frac{5}{2}m}-\frac{-\frac{1}{m}-1\cdot\frac{1}{m}-2}{1\cdot2\times\frac{7}{2}m}a^{1-7m}z^{7m}+
          \frac{\frac{1}{m}-1\cdot\frac{1}{m}-2\cdot\frac{1}{m}-3}{1\cdot2\cdot3\times\frac{9}{2}m}a^{1-9m}z^{9m}
          etc. +
            a,\overline{\frac{1}{\frac{3}{2}m}-\frac{\frac{1}{m}-1}{\frac{5}{2}m}+\frac{\frac{1}{m}-1\cdot\frac{1}{m}-2}{1\cdot2\times\frac{7}{2}m}-\frac{-\frac{1}{m}-1\cdot\frac{1}{m}-2\cdot\frac{1}{m}-3}{1\cdot2\cdot3\times\frac{7}{2}m}}
          etc.;
            u=-\frac{2y^{2+m}}{2+ma^{1+m}}-\frac{a^{1-3m}}{3m}z^{3m}+\frac{\frac{1}{2m}-1}{5m}a^{1-5m}z^{5m}-\frac{\frac{1}{2m}-1,\frac{1}{2m}-2}{1\cdot2\times7m}a^{1-7m}z^{7m}+\frac{\frac{1}{2m}-1,\frac{1}{2m}-2,\frac{1}{2m}-3}{1\cdot2\cdot3\times9m}a^{1-9m}z^{9m}
          etc. +
            aM\cdot\frac{1}{3m}-\frac{\frac{1}{2m}-1}{5m}+\frac{\frac{1}{2m}-1,\frac{1}{2m}-2}{1\cdot2\times7m}-\frac{\frac{1}{2m}-1\cdot\frac{1}{2m}-2\cdot\frac{1}{2m}-3}{1\cdot2\cdot3\times9m}
          etc.;
